## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 2 (systemic — affects all 10 tests) |
| **Medium** | 2 |
| **Low** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. All 10 public methods of `ProductCatalog` are called — one test per method, in declaration order — achieving ~95% line coverage while verifying almost nothing. A bug in any method (wrong price calculation, CSV parsing error, search returning wrong results) would **not** cause any test to fail.

---

### 🔴 Critical

#### 1. Coverage Touching (systemic — all 10 tests)

The entire class follows a pattern of calling every public method without meaningful assertions. 6 of 10 tests have **zero assertions**; the other 4 only assert `IsNotNull` on a return value that can never be null given the implementation.

| Test | Assertion | What it *should* verify |
|------|-----------|------------------------|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17) | *(none)* | Product is retrievable after add |
| `GetProduct_Works` (L23) | `IsNotNull` only | Returned product has correct SKU, Name, Price |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L31) | *(none)* | Price actually changed to 14.99 |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L38) | *(none)* | Product is no longer retrievable |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (L45) | `IsNotNull` only | Results contain 1 match, correct product |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (L54) | `IsNotNull` only | Collection contains 1 product |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L62) | *(none)* | Count equals expected value |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68) | *(none)* | Prices reduced by 10% |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (L76) | `IsNotNull` only | CSV string contains correct data |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L84) | *(none)* | Imported product is retrievable with correct fields |

**Example fix — `UpdatePrice_Works`:**

```csharp
// BEFORE (line 31-36): calls UpdatePrice, asserts nothing
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
}

// AFTER: verifies the price actually changed
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ExistingProduct_PriceIsUpdated()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}
```

**Example fix — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works`:**

